💡 Why OFF/BEAT is rewriting the rules of startups.

Aman Gupta new venture, OFF/BEAT, signals a huge shift in how businesses are built: from product-first → audience-first.

With ₹100 crore funding and top investors like Bessemer Venture Partners, OFF/BEAT shows us the future isn’t about having the best product, it’s about attention + community.

Here’s what we can learn:
1️⃣ boAt Lifestyle taught us: Branding & distribution often matter more than the product.
2️⃣ New playbook: Build the audience & community first → launch products they actually want. Distribution comes ready-made.
3️⃣ Future mantra: Community first, commerce later. Attention drives distribution; distribution drives power.

🎯 The takeaway is clear: The next wave of successful brands won’t chase products, they’ll grow loyal audiences first.

💬 As Aman Gupta proves:
The brand of the future won’t be the one with the best product. It will be the one with an existing audience.
